<div class="post-date">Jun 20</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/1097.html" title="Help save NPR and PBS"> Help save NPR and PBS</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>If you like public television or public radio, now is the time to act as the House of Representatives is planning to slash the budget. <a href="www.moveon.org">MoveOn.org</a> is rallying to protect PBS and NPR from budget cuts through a petition on which they hope to get 1 million signatures.</p>

	<p>When I was attending college at Miami University, I worked in the news department of the public radio station WMUB. The experience was by far the best journalism experience I ever had. When I found a story, they gave me the air time to tell it right. You just can&#8217;t find that anywhere else on the radio dial.</p>

	<p>Why do I favor public funding for NPR? Radio media today is highly consolidated supported by and subservient to its advertisers. There are certainly a number of really good stations that don&#8217;t let ad dollars interfere with its reporting, but if you want news that serves you public radio is the place to get it.</p>

	<p>PBS speaks for itself as the number of kids who have learned courtesies and their letters and numbers from Seseme St. is incalculable. Schools across the nation use PBS programming in their lesson plans.</p>

	<p>The bottom line is this is valuable to me. I believe it makes our communities stronger. I encourage you to sign this <a href="http://www.moveon.org">petition</a>. It should be the top link on the page.</p>

	<p><b>Sidenote</b>: These kinds of cuts were considered in 1995 and a similar petition was circulated. However, once the threat subsided, the petition continued to circulate and it was soon labeled as a hoax. However, this is real and the vote will take place in the next few days. That&#8217;s why I&#8217;m linking only to the homepage of Moveon.org. If the petition is not the top link on the page, it&#8217;s too late for this round.</p>




 
<div class="line"></div>

<div class="smallcat">Posted in <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?c=Politics">Politics</a></div>
<div class="smalluser"> by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a></div>
